We don't have enough people to staff it.

1557
02:27:22,584 --> 02:27:27,647
That's a division that should have at least six patrol officers and two sergeants in it, and it could work.

1558
02:27:28,241 --> 02:27:31,765
day and evening, and there's so much more we could do with that.

1559
02:27:32,486 --> 02:27:38,193
We bring back motorcycles within that, and we should have a lot of departments.

1560
02:27:38,233 --> 02:27:40,175
They used to have what's called CAT teams.

1561
02:27:40,195 --> 02:27:42,358
They're called community action teams.

1562
02:27:42,418 --> 02:27:44,821
Years ago, we had community police officers in different areas.

1563
02:27:45,842 --> 02:27:50,386
because our numbers over the years were dropping, this was a good way to make a team of community officers.

1564
02:27:50,846 --> 02:28:05,237
So a CAT team is a community action team where you have officers who will work in various areas of the city where needed, get out there, get them to know the public, and also get them to act on specific problems that arise in those areas.

1565
02:28:05,917 --> 02:28:08,239
But those are all goals right now.

1566
02:28:08,860 --> 02:28:09,280
For sure.

1567
02:28:09,400 --> 02:28:11,782
And the reason I ask is, you know, I personally,

1568
02:28:13,388 --> 02:28:20,291
I personally don't think we should have books that say there's 112 people when we know seven of them are funded for a dollar and it's really 105.

1569
02:28:20,791 --> 02:28:26,113
Because I think, to your point, right, and we hear it from every department, heard it from FIRE, heard it from you tonight.

1570
02:28:27,254 --> 02:28:30,275
Certainly we hear it from some of the smaller departments in the city.

1571
02:28:32,496 --> 02:28:38,738
The austerity and the budget cuts that have come to municipal government impact all of our departments.

1572
02:28:41,508 --> 02:28:52,737
really the main issue that we're facing right now, whether it's our operating needs and our personnel or our capital needs, is that there is a huge gap between the money we need to spend and the money that we bring in.

1573
02:28:53,177 --> 02:28:59,382
We need to have significantly higher expenditures if we want the things that you just said, right?

1574
02:28:59,562 --> 02:29:06,188
And to me, and it's a difference of opinion that I've raised earlier in our conversation with the mayor and

1575
