1576
02:29:15,974 --> 02:29:21,056
But then you read the asterisk and it's 105 because it's a real issue.

1577
02:29:22,476 --> 02:29:29,919
We're facing really significant, you know, we have, you know, we can talk about the budget deficit, the funds deficit.

1578
02:29:29,939 --> 02:29:30,920
We have a needs deficit.

1579
02:29:30,980 --> 02:29:36,022
There are a bunch of things that we need that are in deficit and we do not have the money to pay for them because,

1580
02:29:36,855 --> 02:29:41,138
The cost of providing those services is going up faster than the revenue that the city brings in.

1581
02:29:41,978 --> 02:29:45,100
That's basically the whole budget problem in four sentences.

1582
02:29:45,840 --> 02:29:47,301
And there's two ways to bring money in.

1583
02:29:47,641 --> 02:29:49,842
You can ask the residents if they want to pay more.

1584
02:29:49,862 --> 02:29:59,928
And if we say, let's say we put something forward that said we think we need six patrol officers and two sergeants to fully staff a traffic division so we can address the dangerous drivers on our streets.

1585
02:29:59,948 --> 02:30:03,230
Because we know the dangerous drivers on our streets are an incredibly big problem.

1586
02:30:03,650 --> 02:30:05,331
We get tons of communications about it.

1587
02:30:07,572 --> 02:30:09,292
That's having the honest conversation.

1588
02:30:09,312 --> 02:30:09,892
We have a need.

1589
02:30:10,133 --> 02:30:12,173
This is how much it costs the voters.

1590
02:30:12,253 --> 02:30:12,833
Can you do that?

1591
02:30:13,193 --> 02:30:16,234
And they can say no, and then we can say that's where we're at.

1592
02:30:17,494 --> 02:30:27,516
The other side of it is trying to bring in more of the new growth because the only way that we can raise revenue without increasing the tax burden on the existing taxpayer is to bring in new development.

1593
02:30:28,436 --> 02:30:29,897
So those are our options.

1594
02:30:30,957 --> 02:30:36,878
You don't make that decision, but I think you illustrated the point well, and I personally

1595
02:30:37,655 --> 02:30:41,698
I understand the intent behind saying we'd like to, that's where we want to be.

1596
02:30:41,959 --> 02:30:44,841
That's where we think we can do more with 112 than with 105.

1597
02:30:45,341 --> 02:30:49,064
But I just have some issues on my own of putting that in a dollar.

1598
02:30:49,425 --> 02:30:50,586
It's aspirational for sure.

1599
02:30:50,606 --> 02:30:53,008
I just think there's maybe a different way to show that aspiration.

1600
02:30:53,568 --> 02:30:55,490
So, thank you.

1601
