1759
02:41:18,709 --> 02:41:23,331
Good evening, esteemed members of city council and the Memphis community.

1760
02:41:24,012 --> 02:41:30,615
This evening, we are going to present to you our fiscal year 27 operating budget that was approved by school committee on May 12.

1761
02:41:32,275 --> 02:41:45,006
As stated during that meeting, this presentation is a responsible, thoughtful, and authentic representation of the work that we have undertaken to support the growth and development of every student in Medford Public Schools.

1762
02:41:46,127 --> 02:41:49,029
This budget cycle follows a year of significant progress.

1763
02:41:50,242 --> 02:41:53,683
Much of it was made possible by the passage of the override last year.

1764
02:41:54,604 --> 02:42:09,330
We continue to successfully operationalize our instructional vision through new consolidated schedules at the elementary, middle, and high school levels, which added 15 minutes of instructional time across the district.

1765
02:42:10,330 --> 02:42:25,942
These changes, alongside our commitment to our collective bargaining agreements with teachers and paraprofessionals, are not only direct reflections of the override implementation, but also they are deeply rooted in our core values of belonging.

1766
02:42:27,222 --> 02:42:37,230
I do think it's very important to note that all of the work associated within the override was not one-time spending, but rather reoccurring costs.

1767
02:42:38,546 --> 02:42:43,327
However, we must also address the realities of the current economic landscape.

1768
02:42:43,907 --> 02:42:56,950
And like many districts across the Commonwealth, and like many of the comments here this evening, we are navigating unavoidable costs, such as rising costs to special education, transportation, and our operational costs.

1769
02:42:57,730 --> 02:43:04,471
To meet these challenges, we as the leadership team have continued to work alongside our school and department leaders.

1770
02:43:05,880 --> 02:43:12,145
to ensure that there is alignment with our evolving needs for our students, our staff, and our community.

1771
02:43:14,146 --> 02:43:19,871
All budget work is iterative, and it's really important to just make sure we mention that because it is still evolving.

1772
02:43:21,212 --> 02:43:28,618
But it is a testament to our values of consistency and coherence that we are working really hard to establish in Medford Public Schools.

1773
02:43:30,376 --> 02:43:39,044
Tonight, this proposal is a result of months of discussion, public feedback, and collaborative problem solving from the entire administrative team.

1774
02:43:39,925 --> 02:43:43,488
I want to thank our budget analyst, Mr. Jerry McHugh, our

1775
